Java regular expressions defining acceptable values are in the source
code for the org.archive.crawler.datamodel.CrawlOrder class:

     // must include a bot name and info URL
     private static String ACCEPTABLE_USER_AGENT =
         &quot;&#92;&#92;S+.*&#92;&#92;(&#92;&#92;+http://&#92;&#92;S*&#92;&#92;).*&quot;;
     // must include a contact email address
     private static String ACCEPTABLE_FROM = &quot;&#92;&#92;S+@&#92;&#92;S+&#92;&#92;.&#92;&#92;S+&quot;;

Looking back at the error you received:

 &gt;&gt;You must set the User-Agent and From HTTP header values to acceptable
 &gt;&gt;strings.
 &gt;&gt; User-Agent: [software-name](+[info-url])[misc]
 &gt;&gt; From: [email-address]

[software-name] may be replaced with any text that does not start
                 with whitespace
[info-url] must be an HTTP url about *your* crawling project. It should
            include contact information, so that if your crawling causes
            problems for crawled sites they can contact you.
[misc] can be any string (or empty)

As already mentioned, you must include the parentheses and &#39;+&#39;.

Google&#39;s crawler has traditionally used a user-agent string like:

&quot;googlebot/2.1 (+http://www.googlebot.com/bot.html)&quot;

This fits the format required by Heritrix.

